{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6bafda8b-a162-4ebf-90b9-6f4f630bd542","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| Switch away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| Switch back | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| Close/kill | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` → `Destroying` |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is **iOS/Mac Catalyst only** — use it to save state before the OS may terminate your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5d324501-ff03-4178-889b-3c62cf0edfd0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":412,"requestId":"4842:2ADC27:74A854F:80FAB71:69F3FAD5"},"id":"cbe4c1b2-e6a2-41b3-a64f-0e077b7a3c5d","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:10.620Z","parentId":"9e880c9b-3050-48a5-810e-7d40d8ac119e"}
